text: Edna Lilian Child (later Tinegate, born 10 October 1922) is a British diver. She won a gold medal at the 1950 British Empire Games and a bronze at the 1938 European Championships and finished sixth at the 1948 Summer Olympics. ==References== Category:1922 births Category:Living people Category:Olympians for Great Britain Category:British divers Category:Sportspeople from London
